Numerals
Kharosthi included a set of numerals that are reminiscent of Roman numerals. The system is based on an additive and a multiplicative principle, but does not have the subtractive feature used in the Roman numeral system.
The numerals, like the letters, are written from right to left. There is no zero and no separate signs for the digits 5â€“9.  Numbers in Kharosthi use an additive system.
For example, the number 1996 would be written as 1000 4 4 1 100 20 20 20 20 10 4 2 (image: , text: ğ©‡ğ©ƒğ©ƒğ©€ğ©†ğ©…ğ©…ğ©…ğ©…ğ©„ğ©ƒğ©).

